author: danj
msg: Fix for MUSE-28 - we now do routing solely on WS-A Action URI. This required significant change
to the SimpleResourceDescriptor implementation class and SimpleResource. Because of WSDL4J and
DOM's use of String for URIs, I've updated a number of core methods to use String instead of URI
because the URI wasn't providing any additional value and was only adding more boilerplate code
URI has been left in key places (like WS-A EndpointReference) where the
validation and different URI parts are key to implementation and semantics. So far, this change
has only had an affect on client implemetnation classes, so anyone with client code should not
see any compilation errors. The only place one might see compilation errors is from proxies
generated with Andrew's current codegen contribution, which hasn't been updated yet to reflect
this change. I have made the appropriate change locally and will include it when I commit his
